# Command obsidian

## What does this command do:

Anything you can do in Obsidian you can do from the command line

## Installed from

For Fedora install using: Download AppImage from https://obsidian.md/download, run it, then enable CLI in Settings → General → "Command line interface" and follow on-screen instructions (copies binary to ~/.local/bin/obsidian)
For Raspberry Pi install using: Download AppImage from https://obsidian.md/download, run it, then enable CLI in Settings → General → "Command line interface" and follow on-screen instructions (copies binary to ~/.local/bin/obsidian)
For Mac install using: Download from https://obsidian.md/download, install app, then enable CLI in Settings → General → "Command line interface" and follow on-screen instructions (creates symlink at /usr/local/bin/obsidian)

## Command path

For Fedora run: ~/.local/bin/obsidian
For Raspberry Pi run: ~/.local/bin/obsidian
For Mac run: /usr/local/bin/obsidian

## Command documentation

Docs can be found at https://obsidian.md/cli

## Notes

- Obsidian app must be running for commands to work
- `file=` resolves by name (like wikilinks); `path=` is exact (folder/note.md)
- Most commands default to the active file when file/path is omitted
- Quote values with spaces: `name="My Note"`
- Use `\n` for newline, `\t` for tab in content values
- Target a specific vault: `vault=<name>` (global option)

## Command options

### Files
```
obsidian read file=<name>                    # Read file contents
obsidian read path=<folder/note.md>          # Read file by exact path
obsidian create name=<name> content=<text>   # Create a new file
obsidian create name=<name> template=<name>  # Create from template
obsidian open file=<name>                    # Open a file in Obsidian
obsidian open file=<name> newtab             # Open in a new tab
obsidian append file=<name> content=<text>   # Append content to a file
obsidian prepend file=<name> content=<text>  # Prepend content to a file
obsidian delete file=<name>                  # Delete a file (to trash)
obsidian delete file=<name> permanent        # Delete permanently
obsidian move file=<name> to=<path>          # Move or rename a file
obsidian rename file=<name> name=<newname>   # Rename a file
obsidian file file=<name>                    # Show file info
obsidian files                               # List all files in vault
obsidian files folder=<path>                 # List files in a folder
obsidian files ext=md                        # List files by extension
obsidian wordcount file=<name>               # Count words and characters
```

